replies.bodyText:
Yeah, 10 or statements is not ideal. Typically you would put all the extensions into a list/array and then iterate through them to check if any of them is a match.
At the very least you should change the code so that you are not calling toLowercase 10 times.
I suggest doing something like this:
private static final Set<String> PHOTO_EXTENSIONS = Set.of(".jpg",".jpeg",".png",...);

private static boolean hasPhotoExt(String str){
    String lstr = str.toLowercase();
    return PHOTO_EXTENSIONS.stream().anyMatch(lstr::endsWith);
}
